main event: An object was observed traveling from Toledo, Ohio to Lake Erie at a high rate of speed, estimated around 600 knots.
interesting points: The object was observed for 45 minutes.
The object was seen by pilots of separate airlines.
The object traveled from Toledo, Ohio to Selfridge AFB, Michigan in one minute, at an estimated speed of 4,500 knots.
The sighting was observed under thin high clouds and good visibility.
The object's size, shape, or color could not be determined.
